        "text": "## Ranking: log K₁ with Thiocyanate (SCN⁻)\n\n| Metal | log K₁ | Conditions (T, I) | Source |\n|-------|--------|--------------------|--------|\n| **Hg²⁺** | **9.64** | 25 °C, I = 0 M | SRD-46 (vlm_172457) |\n| Cd²⁺ | 1.93 | 25 °C, I = 0 M | SRD-46 (vlm_172411) |\n| Pb²⁺ | 1.08* | 25 °C, I = 4 M | SRD-46 (vlm_172486) |\n\n\\* No I = 0 value available for Pb²⁺; at I = 1 M, log K₁ = 0.49. Even extrapolated to zero ionic strength, Pb²⁺ remains the weakest binder.\n\n\n**Hg²⁺ ≫ Cd²⁺ > Pb²⁺**\n\n**Mercury(II) has by far the highest affinity for thiocyanate**, with a log K₁ of **9.64** — nearly 8 orders of magnitude larger than those of Cd²⁺ (1.93) and Pb²⁺ (~0.5–1.1).",
